  "description": "The mechanical aspects of hydration in FLAC3D are handled by a modified Drucker-Prager constitutive model where elastic and strength properties depend on the hydration grade, \\(\\alpha\\) (Hinze 1987). [ * ] Due to a dormant phase, the evolution of strength and stiffness starts with some delay. This is taken into account by the minimum degree of hydration, \\(\\alpha_0\\) . This value marks the transition between the suspension and solid-state behavior. Beyond \\(\\alpha_0\\) , strength and stiffness do not always depend linearly on hydration grade. Thus, a relationship is introduced, based on the ide",
